Here's the answer.

00:56:38.697 --> 00:56:41.030
First of all, she's a senior
counselor to the president.

00:56:41.030 --> 00:56:42.560
So if there is
something going on

00:56:42.560 --> 00:56:46.615
and we want answers
to questions,

00:56:46.615 --> 00:56:48.490
other than the president,
who hasn't given me

00:56:48.490 --> 00:56:51.040
an interview since the
Judge Curiel questions

00:56:51.040 --> 00:56:55.750
that I asked him
in June 2016, there

00:56:55.750 --> 00:56:57.910
isn't anyone necessarily better.

00:56:57.910 --> 00:57:00.400
And Sunday was, I
had questions about--

00:57:03.200 --> 00:57:03.760
what was it?

00:57:03.760 --> 00:57:04.810
I guess, Michael Cohen.

00:57:04.810 --> 00:57:05.980
I forget.

00:57:05.980 --> 00:57:10.360
300 scandals ago, but
there was something.

00:57:10.360 --> 00:57:15.280
Oh, it was, yeah, Rudy Giuliani
had basically let the cat out

00:57:15.280 --> 00:57:16.984
of the bag that the
president had lied.

00:57:16.984 --> 00:57:19.150
AUDIENCE: Yeah, but it
didn't matter what you asked.

00:57:19.150 --> 00:57:19.340
JAKE TAPPER: Thank you.

00:57:19.340 --> 00:57:20.006
I appreciate it.

00:57:20.006 --> 00:57:21.496
Thank you so much.

00:57:21.496 --> 00:57:22.870
I'm not above
being fact checked.

00:57:22.870 --> 00:57:25.150
I appreciate it.

00:57:25.150 --> 00:57:27.310
So how do you explain this?

00:57:27.310 --> 00:57:28.740
So that's one.

00:57:28.740 --> 00:57:31.990
Two, I thought it
was interesting

00:57:31.990 --> 00:57:35.080
that the premise of
all my questions,

00:57:35.080 --> 00:57:38.260
accurate, but also
a premise was,

00:57:38.260 --> 00:57:40.630
the president lies so much.

